# Restart dev server after tasks

After finishing an implementation, fix, or refactor task in this repo, restart the local Django development server so changes are picked up reliably.

## When to restart

Restart when the task changed any of:

- Python code (`apps/`, `config/`, `manage.py`)
- templates (`templates/`)
- static files (`static/`)
- migrations or settings

Skip restart for read-only tasks (exploration, reviews, questions with no code changes).

## How to restart on Windows

1. Stop any process listening on port `8000`.
2. Start the server again from the project root.

Use PowerShell:

```powershell
Get-NetTCPConnection -LocalPort 8000 -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | ForEach-Object { Stop-Process -Id $_.OwningProcess -Force -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue }
cd "e:\laragon\www\personal-finance"
python manage.py runserver
```

Prefer project venv Python when present:

- `venv\Scripts\python.exe manage.py runserver`
- `.venv\Scripts\python.exe manage.py runserver`

Run the server in the background and verify it responds at `http://127.0.0.1:8000/`.

## Completion checklist

Before ending the response:

1. Restart was performed (or skipped with a brief reason).
2. Mention the server URL if it was restarted.
